@selvaganesang 
If the mxosrvr dies quickly due to some issue (say 6 times within a minute), then dcs server would not restart it again, because we think it is the vicious behavior that kill the mxosrvr.
If the mxosrvr dies slowly (say 5 times in 25 minutes and 6th time after many hours), dcs server will restart the mxosrvr.

I re-read the relevant code. I fully understood its meaning:
1. rc is from checkAndSplit param, and set the value to EXE_OK by: 
    *rc = EXE_OK;
    so the rc must be not NULL, I think this may be an agreement
2. the method Cluster maybe set result to rc, may be not because fail when call new
    so we must check the *rc is set or not.
    don't need to check the rc is NULL or not.

So I think it should be wrote like this:
  if ( !next_ || *rc ) {
    if ( ! (*rc) )  * rc = EXE_NO_MEM_TO_EXEC;
    return TRUE;
  }

what do you think?

If there was an initialization *rc = EXE_OK already, then this code should be

if (!next_) {
   *rc = EXE_NO_MEM_TO_EXEC;
    return TRUE;
}

Sorry for not reviewing the surround code earlier.
